# 6. 怖い

Mizuki: (Well, it's over...)
Mizuki: (I still couldn't really get my head around it...)
Mizuki: (Anyway, what should I watch next...?)
Mizuki: ...
Mizuki: (I don't wanna do anything.)
Mizuki: (But I don't have the courage to just disappear either.)
Mizuki: (And yet, I don't see the point in living.)
Mizuki: (Which is why watching anime like this works, because...)
Mizuki: I don't have to think about anything.
Mizuki: (Who's messaging me at this hour...?)
Mizuki: An...?
Mizuki: ...
Mizuki: (I wonder if Ena's still trying to get a hold of me.)
Mizuki: (I've been logged out of Nightcord ever since that day, so I really don't know.)
???: <Mizuki.>
Mizuki: MEIKO...?
MEIKO: <Finally, we can talk...>
Mizuki: What happened to keeping your distance from us...?
MEIKO: <...>
MEIKO: <Are you not coming back to SEKAI?>
MEIKO: <Everyone's been waiting for you...>
Mizuki: I know.
Mizuki: But...
Mizuki: ...
Mizuki: I can't...
MEIKO: <Mizuki...>
Kanade: Where could Mizuki be...?
Mafuyu: We've been to all the usual places we could come up with, but it is possible that we keep just missing each other...
Luka: How do you know that Mizuki's left home at all...?
Ena: I mean...
Kanade: We have to keep looking.
Kanade: That's all we can do right now.
Len: ...
KAITO: If only we could reach Mizuki's phone somehow.
Ena: ...
Ena: MEIKO...!
Rin: Where were you?
MEIKO: With Mizuki.
Ena: What...?!
Ena: B-But you said you always ended up somewhere pitch black whenever you tried going over to Mizuki's phone...
MEIKO: I managed to pop in when it was actually in use.
MEIKO: And we had a chance to talk a little.
Kanade: Really...?
Ena: Thanks so much, MEIKO...!
Ena: So, where's Mizuki been all this time?
MEIKO: Apparently, at home...
MEIKO: For a few days at the very least...
Ena: I knew it...
Ena: Then, what's our next angle...?
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu: Supplementary classes. Although, I'm not sure Mizuki's actually going to show up for them...
Ena: What...?
Mafuyu: I happened to run into Aoyagi during my search.
Mafuyu: Based on my conversation with him, Mizuki's missed enough days to have to attend supplementary classes.
Kanade: Come to think of it, I remember hearing something about having to attend supplementary classes or risk being held back.
Mafuyu: Considering how Mizuki's just barely been staying in contact with Shiraishi...
Mafuyu: I'm guessing it has something to do with not wanting others to worry.
Ena: So...
Ena: Mizuki's worried that getting held back would cause trouble for everyone?
Mafuyu: I don't know for certain.
Ena: (It's true that Mizuki might be feeling that way, and it would explain those messages with Shiraishi. Still...)
Ena: (Is Mizuki really going to show up...?)
Ena: (No, I have to take whatever I can at this point...)
Ena: Thanks, Mafuyu. I'll try asking the teachers about those supplementary classes!
Ena: Also, MEIKO.
Ena: I'm really sorry, but would you keep being by Mizuki's side if possible?
MEIKO: I can.
Ena: Thanks.
Ena: Yeah, I've got things covered here. Thanks again for coming.
Ena: But still no sign... Mizuki seems to come here just after noon, so we can probably expect to keep waiting until the last minute.
Kanade's Voice: <Okay. In that case, I'll stay near the school gate a little while longer.>
Ena: Thanks.
Ena: I'm sorry for making you skip school like this, Mafuyu...
Mafuyu's Voice: <It's okay. This is far more important.>
Ena: You mean that? Thanks...
Ena: Anyway, I'll let you know if something happens.
Ena: (Today's when the teachers said there'd be supplementary classes...)
Ena: (I've been looking all over for Mizuki since then, but we never once saw each other.)
Ena: (Still, today might be my biggest chance...)
Ena: (Those supplementary classes are supposed to take place after school, so Mizuki should, in theory, be arriving soon.)
Ena: I want us to talk.
Ena: (If I'm going to maximize my odds, should I wait by the main entrance instead of by this classroom?)
Ena: (I don't know, but I'd rather not miss my chance by moving around needlessly.)
Ena: (Still, is Mizuki really coming...?)
Ena: (But this is basically my last shot. I have to bet everything on it.)
Ena: (I don't have a choice... Right...?)
Ena: (But is this really what I'm supposed to be doing...?)
Ena: (Waiting here for...)
Ena: *Gasp*
Ena: <Sorry, you two. I have a huge favor to ask...!>
